race.comment: TOTAL FRANKY (1) had been in top form scoring three consecutive wins before a minor placing (21.78) last time at this track. Form here at this distance is sound. Has the inside draw and looks tough to beat. JIMMY ROO (7) is worth forgiving last start after finishing eighth (29.22) from Box 2 at this track over 498m. Boasts a strong record from this draw with five wins and four minor placings from 11 starts. Key runner on best form. DRINK SHIRAZ (2) could manage only seventh at this track last time but turned heads when posting a flying 21.76 over 380m at this track the start prior. Expected to feature on best figures. JUDI STARLINE (8) placed last time and is worth some thought.
